---
import '../styles/global.css';
import CookieConsent from '../components/CookieConsent.astro';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <title>Cookie Policy — CV Mold Testing</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Cookie Policy for CV Mold Testing LLC. Learn about the cookies we use and how to manage your preferences."
    />
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://cvmoldtesting.com/cookie-policy" />
    <meta name="robots" content="noindex, follow" />
  </head>
  <body class="bg-white">
    <header class="bg-white border-b border-[#E7E3E4] px-6 py-4">
      <a href="/"><img src="/logo.svg" alt="CV Mold Testing" /></a>
    </header>

    <main class="mx-auto max-w-200 px-6 py-16 mb-20">
      <h1 class="mb-4 text-4xl font-semibold text-[#2C2F47]">Cookie Policy</h1>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-snug text-gray-700">
        <strong>Last Updated:</strong> May 14, 2026
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-8 mb-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900">
        1. What Are Cookies?
      </h2>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-snug text-gray-700">
        Cookies are small text files placed on your computer or mobile device
        when you visit a website. They are widely used to make websites work
        efficiently and provide information to website owners.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-8 mb-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900">
        2. How We Use Cookies
      </h2>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-snug text-gray-700">
        We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to track activity on
        our website and store certain information. The tracking technologies we
        use include beacons, tags, and scripts to collect and track information
        and to improve and analyze our website.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-8 mb-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900">
        3. Types of Cookies We Use
      </h2>

      <h3 class="mt-5 mb-2 text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">
        3.1 Essential Cookies
      </h3>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-snug text-gray-700">
        These cookies are necessary for the website to function properly. They
        enable basic functions like page navigation and access to secure areas.
      </p>
      <ul class="mb-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
        <li class="text-gray-700">
          Session cookies that maintain your connection during your visit
        </li>
        <li class="text-gray-700">
          Security cookies that help identify and prevent security risks
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-snug text-gray-700">
        <strong>Duration:</strong> Session-based (deleted when you close your browser)
      </p>

      <h3 class="mt-5 mb-2 text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">
        3.2 Analytics Cookies
      </h3>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-snug text-gray-700">
        We use analytics cookies to understand how visitors interact with our
        website. These cookies help us improve the user experience by providing
        insights into which pages are visited most frequently.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-2 leading-snug text-gray-700">
        <strong>Services We Use:</strong>
      </p>
      <ul class="mb-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
        <li class="text-gray-700">
          <strong>Google Analytics</strong> (via Google Tag Manager): Tracks website
          traffic, user behavior, and demographics.
        </li>
        <li class="text-gray-700">
          <strong>Google Tag Manager:</strong> Manages analytics and marketing tags
          on our website.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mb-2 leading-snug text-gray-700">
        <strong>Information Collected:</strong>
      </p>
      <ul class="mb-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
        <li class="text-gray-700">Pages visited</li>
        <li class="text-gray-700">Time spent on pages</li>
        <li class="text-gray-700">Browser type and version</li>
        <li class="text-gray-700">Device information</li>
        <li class="text-gray-700">Geographic location (city/state level)</li>
        <li class="text-gray-700">Referring websites</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-snug text-gray-700">
        <strong>Duration:</strong> Varies by cookie, typically 30 days to 2 years
      </p>
      <p class="mb-2 leading-snug text-gray-700">
        <strong>Third-Party Privacy Policies:</strong>
      </p>
      <ul class="mb-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
        <li class="text-gray-700">
          Google Analytics & Tag Manager:
          <a
            href="https://policies.google.com/privacy"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-[#2C2F47] hover:underline"
            >https://policies.google.com/privacy</a
          >
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="mt-5 mb-2 text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">
        3.3 Marketing / Advertising Cookies
      </h3>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-snug text-gray-700">
        These cookies are used to deliver advertisements more relevant to you
        and to measure the effectiveness of our advertising campaigns.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-2 leading-snug text-gray-700">
        <strong>Services We Use:</strong>
      </p>
      <ul class="mb-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
        <li class="text-gray-700">
          <strong>Google Ads:</strong> For remarketing and conversion tracking
        </li>
        <li class="text-gray-700">
          <strong>Facebook Pixel (Meta Pixel):</strong> Tracks conversions from Facebook
          ads and enables remarketing
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-snug text-gray-700">
        <strong>Duration:</strong> Varies, typically 30 days to 2 years
      </p>
      <p class="mb-2 leading-snug text-gray-700">
        <strong>Third-Party Privacy Policies:</strong>
      </p>
      <ul class="mb-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
        <li class="text-gray-700">
          Meta/Facebook:
          <a
            href="https://www.facebook.com/privacy/explanation"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-[#2C2F47] hover:underline"
            >https://www.facebook.com/privacy/explanation</a
          >
        </li>
        <li class="text-gray-700">
          Google Ads:
          <a
            href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-[#2C2F47] hover:underline"
            >https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads</a
          >
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="mt-8 mb-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900">
        4. Third-Party Cookies
      </h2>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-snug text-gray-700">
        Third-party service providers such as Google and Meta may also place
        cookies on your device through our website. We do not control these
        cookies and recommend reviewing their privacy policies:
      </p>
      <ul class="mb-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
        <li class="text-gray-700">
          <strong>Google:</strong>
          <a
            href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/cookies"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-[#2C2F47] hover:underline"
            >https://policies.google.com/technologies/cookies</a
          >
        </li>
        <li class="text-gray-700">
          <strong>Meta/Facebook:</strong>
          <a
            href="https://www.facebook.com/privacy/policies/cookies"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-[#2C2F47] hover:underline"
            >https://www.facebook.com/privacy/policies/cookies</a
          >
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="mt-8 mb-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900">
        5. How to Manage Cookies
      </h2>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-snug text-gray-700">
        You have the right to accept or reject cookies. Most browsers
        automatically accept cookies, but you can modify your settings to
        decline them.
      </p>

      <h3 class="mt-5 mb-2 text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">
        5.1 Browser Settings
      </h3>
      <ul class="mb-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
        <li class="text-gray-700">
          <strong>Chrome:</strong> Settings › Privacy and security › Cookies and other
          site data
        </li>
        <li class="text-gray-700">
          <strong>Firefox:</strong> Settings › Privacy & Security › Cookies and Site
          Data
        </li>
        <li class="text-gray-700">
          <strong>Safari:</strong> Preferences › Privacy › Cookies and website data
        </li>
        <li class="text-gray-700">
          <strong>Edge:</strong> Settings › Cookies and site permissions
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="mt-5 mb-2 text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">
        5.2 Opt-Out Tools
      </h3>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-snug text-gray-700">
        You can opt out of Google Analytics by installing the browser add-on:
        <a
          href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="text-[#2C2F47] hover:underline"
          >https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout</a
        >
      </p>

      <h3 class="mt-5 mb-2 text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">
        5.3 Impact of Disabling Cookies
      </h3>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-snug text-gray-700">
        If you disable cookies, some features of our website may not function
        properly. Essential cookies cannot be disabled if you wish to use the
        website.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-8 mb-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900">
        6. Do Not Track Signals
      </h2>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-snug text-gray-700">
        Some browsers include a "Do Not Track" (DNT) feature. Our website does
        not currently respond to DNT signals.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-8 mb-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900">
        7. Updates to This Cookie Policy
      </h2>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-snug text-gray-700">
        We may update this Cookie Policy from time to time. Please check this
        page periodically for updates.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-8 mb-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900">
        8. Contact Us
      </h2>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-snug text-gray-700">
        If you have questions about our use of cookies, please contact us:
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4 leading-snug text-gray-700">
        <strong>CV Mold Testing LLC</strong><br />
        Florida, USA<br />
        Email: <a
          href="mailto:info@cvmoldtesting.com"
          class="text-[#2C2F47] hover:underline">info@cvmoldtesting.com</a
        ><br />
        Phone: <a href="tel:+13053974966" class="text-[#2C2F47] hover:underline"
          >+1 305 397 4966</a
        >
      </p>

      <hr class="my-8 border-gray-300" />
      <p class="mb-4 leading-snug text-gray-700">
        By using our website, you consent to our use of cookies as described in
        this Cookie Policy.
      </p>
    </main>

    <footer class="bg-white border-t border-[#E7E3E4] p-5 pb-11">
      <div
        class="max-w-200 mx-auto flex flex-col gap-y-4 sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-between text-sm text-gray-600"
      >
        <p>© 2026 CV Mold Testing LLC</p>
        <ul class="flex gap-x-4">
          <li>
            <a
              href="/privacy-policy"
              class="hover:text-[#2C2F47] transition-colors">Privacy Policy</a
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            <a
              href="/cookie-policy"
              class="hover:text-[#2C2F47] transition-colors">Cookie Policy</a
            >
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </footer>
    <CookieConsent />
  </body>
</html>
